<http://localhost:8000/notes/linear-algebra/eigenvalues>
    a note:Note ;
    dct:title "Eigenvalues and diagonalization" ;
    note:topic "spectral-theory" ;
    note:course <http://localhost:8000/notes/linear-algebra/> ;
    dct:created "2026-04-21" ;
    note:text "An eigenvector of A is a nonzero v with Av = lv. A is diagonalizable iff it has a basis of eigenvectors; symmetric real matrices always are, by the spectral theorem. Exam hint: characteristic polynomial questions recur every year." .
